<div id="middle">
  <div class="banner">
    <div class="banneroneforth">
      <h1>In App Coupons for Mobile Customers</h1>
      <p>
        Give coupons to your mobile app users intelligently to increase conversion and
        average order size. Show them to only a section of users where it makes
        most sense. Use dashboard to track user adoption in depth.
      </p>

      <% if current_user.blank? %>
        <a class="button-img" href="/signup">Create Campaign</a>
      <% else %>
        <a class="button-img" href="/member/campaigns/twitter">Create Campaign</a>
      <% end %>
    </div>
    <div class="banneronethird">
      <img src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/fbappshq-assets/datas/71045/large.png" />
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="content">
    <div class="features-hig"><h2>Features Highlights</h2>
      <div class="app-feature">
        <ul>
          <li>
            <h5>Easy Integration</h5>
            <p>
              Include our Android SDK once and then you can give any number of coupons
              on your app without ever having to bother engineering team.
              This SDK allows you to run all types of mobile campaigns available through us.
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <h5>Audience Groups</h5>
            <p>
              Create custom audience groups and then run targeted marketing
              campaigns for them e.g. Users who have bought a product on your mobile
              app can be a group and all users who have launched your app more than
              10 times can be another group
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <h5>Launch Instantly</h5>
            <p>
              Launch campaigns with in seconds of including SDK in your app. It
              takes a simple click to turn coupons on/off. Also, you can run multiple
              coupons at the same time - one for each audience group.
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <h5>Custom Styling</h5>
            <p>You can change look and feel of the running campaigns almost 
              instantly by simply going to dashboard and click on few links.
            </p>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>

</div>
